  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What advice do you have for a seventeen year old who is pretty confused in life?",
  "response": "Being confused at seventeen is completely normal. It's a time of transition and self-discovery. Here are some pieces of advice that might help you navigate this confusing period:\n\n1. **Explore Your Interests**: Take the time to try new things. Whether it's a new hobby, sport, or academic subject, exploring different interests can help you discover what you're passionate about.\n\n2. **Seek Guidance**: Don't hesitate to talk to trusted adults like parents, teachers, or counselors. They can offer valuable insights and advice based on their own experiences.\n\n3. **Set Small Goals**: It can be overwhelming to think about your entire future at once. Instead, set small, achievable goals for yourself. These can be as simple as finishing a project or improving a particular skill.\n\n4. **Embrace Learning**: Understand that it's okay not to have all the answers. Embrace learning and see every experience as an opportunity to grow.\n\n5. **Mind Your Mental Health**: Take care of your mental well-being. If you're feeling overwhelmed, consider talking to a mental health professional. It's important to prioritize your mental health.\n\n6. **Stay Open-Minded**: Be open to different paths and possibilities. Sometimes, the best opportunities come when you least expect them.\n\n7. **Build a Support Network**: Surround yourself with positive influences\u2014friends and family who encourage and support you.\n\n8. **Reflect Regularly**: Take time to reflect on your experiences and feelings. Journaling can be a great way to process your thoughts and gain clarity.\n\n9. **Be Patient**: Finding your path in life takes time. Be patient with yourself and understand that it's okay to change your mind and direction along the way.\n\n10. **Stay True to Yourself**: Ultimately, make decisions that align with your values and what makes you happy. Don't feel pressured to follow a path just because others expect it of you.\n\nRemember, everyone's journey is unique, and it's okay to feel confused. With time and exploration, you'll find your way.",
